# SDK Hooks

Files in `src/hooks/` are NOT regenerated by Speakeasy — they are safe to edit.

## User-Agent Format

Pattern: `Cloudinary/{ProductName} {Runtime}/{sdkVersion} Gen/{genVersion} Schema/{schemaVersion} ({systemInfo})`

- `ProductName` is derived from `@cloudinary/{package-name}` → PascalCase (e.g., `AccountProvisioning`)
- `Runtime` is `NodeJS` for this SDK
- Reference old format: `CloudinaryProvisioningNodeJS/0.2.0 (Node 18.x.x)`

## AccountConfig (CLOUDINARY_ACCOUNT_URL)

`accountConfig.ts` parses `CLOUDINARY_ACCOUNT_URL` with format: `account://<api_key>:<api_secret>@<account_id>`

Individual env vars (`CLOUDINARY_PROVISIONING_API_KEY`, `CLOUDINARY_PROVISIONING_API_SECRET`, `CLOUDINARY_ACCOUNT_ID`) override URL-parsed values.
